Based on our [CONFDEV|https://developer.atlassian.com/display/CONFDEV/Remote+Confluence+Methods] Remote Confluence Methods method, export space permission is not necessary to export a space into PDF format.

{quote}(i) In Confluence 3.0, the remote API specification for PDF exports changed. Consequently, the 'Space - Export' permission above no longer applies to PDF exports. Please refer to Remote API Specification for PDF Export for current remote API details on this feature.{quote}

However our CONF page in regards [exporting space into PDF|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Exporting+Confluence+Pages+and+Spaces+to+PDF] specifically describe that "export space" permission is necessary:

{quote}To use the space export functionality, you need the 'Export Space' permission.{quote}

We have confirmed that the mentioned permission is necessary to create a pdf export space. Hence we believe the information provided on our CONFDEV page is incorrect unless we are missing something.

