It is easy to configure link between a Confluence page and JIRA issue, with only couple of steps. This will leads to a lot of issues and filters being linked to Confluence from JIRA, however there is no way for us to see these relations unless we open the particular issue in JIRA or the particular page in Confluence.

It would be easier and more effective to manage the list of which filters are referenced by which wiki pages, in one configuration page.

* Add a status macro to a page and select the colour to be green.
* Use the following in a space stylesheet: {noformat}                
.aui-lozenge.success {  
  background-color: #CCCCCC;  
}  
{noformat}
* Reload the page

Note that the initial page view has applied the stylesheet, and the macro appears grey, but once the page has finished loading the styling is lost and the macro appears green again.

This happens because the quick comment editor is incorrectly applying the default CSS over the custom CSS. If you turn off comments for the space then the custom CSS will be persisted as expected.

